e an original contribution to new paradigms of historical writing and to stimulate public debate on history writing in a diverse society.&lt;/p>

&lt;p>National histories provide stories of origins, myths of progress,&amp;nbsp;frames of identification and belonging, ways of connecting public and private, past and present. Thomas Babington Macaulay's &lt;em>History of England&lt;/em> has long been recognised as one of the most powerful stories of the nation ever written.&lt;/p>

&lt;p>New archival research on Macaulay, his family, his writings and his public life,&amp;nbsp;will be at the centre of this project - raising questions about the 'island story' that he espoused, and his understanding of the relation between nation and empire.&amp;nbsp;At the same time a variety of ways of engaging with and intervening in public debate over the writing of national histories will be pursued&amp;nbsp;- from the establishment of a seminar series and the organisation of an academic conference to working with teachers and curators, schools, museums and galleries. &lt;/p>

&lt;p>The many events being organised around the bi-centenary of the abolition of the slave trade in 2007 will provide an ideal opportunity to raise questions and encourage debate about what kinds of histories can best represent the plurality of contemporary society.&lt;/p></gtr:abstractText><gtr:fund><gtr:end>2008-09-30</gtr:end><gtr:funder url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/organisation/924BE15C-91F2-4AAD-941A-3F338324B6AE"><gtr:id>924BE15C-91F2-4AAD-941A-3F338324B6AE</gtr:id><gtr:name>ESRC</gtr:name></gtr:funder><gtr:start>2006-10-01</gtr:start><gtr:type>INCOME_ACTUAL</gtr:type><gtr:valuePounds>203885</gtr:valuePounds></gtr:fund><gtr:output><gtr:artisticAndCreativeProductOutputs/><gtr:collaborationOutputs/><gtr:disseminationOutputs><gtr:disseminationOutput><gtr:description>Moira Stewart in search of Mr Wilberforce</gtr:description><gtr:form>A press release, press conference or response to a media enquiry/interview</gtr:form><gtr:geographicReach>National</gtr:geographicReach><gtr:id>E6C1D7C7-320F-4C48-B945-502C84263DAA</gtr:id><gtr:impact>Programme in relation to bi-centenary of abolition of slave trade

